indicator.description:
Project started in 2015.
1. Number of risk-mitigated landslides in target local governments by the end of March 2016; 
2. Number of people and households with restored safe living conditions and livelihoods in target landslide areas by the end of March 2016;
3. Number of disaster-prone local communities with land risk mitigation implementation measures in place;
4. Number of practical manuals/guidelines on landslide monitoring as per international standards designed and disseminated to local governments in the country;
5. Number of local government staff received practical technical and training assistance in the subject matter;
6. Number of conducted comprehensive analysis of the existing legal, institutional and policy framework related to landslide management in Bosnia and Herzegovina.
